about.title: About me
about.primary: Hey there! I'm a graduate of a Full Stack Web Development Bootcamp, and I'm super excited to dive into the world of software and web development! I'm a quick learner and love working with others to achieve project success and keep growing. I've got a strong work ethic, great communication skills, and a knack for putting the user first. Let's create some awesome stuff together!

projects.title: Netflix and Grill
projects.description: I was part of a four person team developing a dynamic date night generator app. This web application utilizes CSS, HTML, and JavaScript to offer a date planning experience. The app integrates a movie database API and a recipe API, allowing users to select a genre of movie and a style of food. In response, the app generates three corresponding movie recommendations and recipes to cook. I was the repository manager, responsible for finding the API's and integrating the recipe API into the front end. I also helped integrate the movie API.

projects.title: Clean & Green
projects.description: I collaborated with a team of three to develop a full-stack application focusing on serving homemade house cleaners. The user selects what area of the house they need cleaners for and the app generates corresponding recipes. We used HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for the front-end and Node.js with Express.js and Sequelize with PostgreSQL for the back-end. I was responsible for building and deploying the API that generated the recipes and integrating it with the front-end.

projects.title: The Play List
projects.description: This was a solo project built entirely in React. This web app uses a video game API to generate video games based on a user search. The page returns the game's key art, title, genres, and Metacritic rating. You are able to search by title, genre, and game system. You are then able to add games to a 'play list' or to a 'completed list' and also give the game a personal rating.
